injuries.long_comment: Doncic took an inadvertent kick to his left calf during Sunday's private workout and underwent an MRI Tuesday after experiencing tightness during Monday's first training camp practice. The MVP candidate will likely miss more than only one exhibition and could be sidelined for the entire preseason schedule. However, per Tim MacMahon of ESPN.com, Doncic is expected to be ready for the regular-season opener against the Spurs on Oct. 24.
injuries.short_comment: Doncic (calf) has been ruled out for Monday's preseason opener against the Grizzlies, NBA writer Marc Stein reports.

injuries.long_comment: Embiid doesn't appear to have suffered any injury but will miss his second straight preseason contest Friday. His next chance to suit up is Saturday's preseason matchup with Boston.
injuries.short_comment: Embiid (rest) didn't make the trip for Friday's preseason contest against the Timberwolves, Tony Jones of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: This isn't the least bit surprising, as Leonard has yet to be cleared for 5-on-5 scrimmaging. The Clippers will continue to bring him along slowly, and it will be interesting to see if Leonard is able to play on Opening Night on Oct. 23 as he previously indicated.
injuries.short_comment: Leonard (knee) will not play in Tuesday's preseason game against the Nets, Law Murray of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: The Lakers are resting LeBron James and Anthony Davis, and the Timberwolves will do the same with Edwards and Julius Randle, so this game will be lacking star power. Edwards is expected to operate as the Timberwolves' go-to player on offense in 2024-25 following the trade that sent Karl-Anthony Towns to the Knicks.
injuries.short_comment: Edwards (rest) won't play in Friday's preseason contest against the Lakers, Dave McMenamin of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: VanVleet will be replaced by Amen Thompson in the starting lineup Wednesday. VanVleet's next opportunity for preseason reps comes against the Pelicans on Tuesday.
injuries.short_comment: VanVleet (rest) will not play in Wednesday's preseason game versus Oklahoma City, Jonathan Feigen of the Houston Chronicle reports.

injuries.long_comment: Fears of Jackson dealing with a hamstring strain have been confirmed, but suffering a low level of severity bodes well for the 25-year-old. Coach Taylor Jenkins fully expects Jackson to be ready for Opening Night, while also noting that the Grizzlies will proceed cautiously with his activity throughout the remainder of training camp.
injuries.short_comment: Jackson (hamstring) is dealing with a low-grade hamstring strain, although there is "no concern" that Jackson could miss Memphis' season opener versus Utah on Oct. 23, Damichael Cole of The Memphis Commercial Appeal reports.

injuries.long_comment: According to coach Taylor Jenkins, the Grizzlies will proceed with caution, but there's no concern for his availability for Opening Night. Morant's status for Thursday's preseason game against Charlotte is up in the air, but it would be surprising to see him take the floor for that contest.
injuries.short_comment: Morant has been diagnosed with a mild ankle sprain, Damichael Cole of The Memphis Commercial Appeal reports.

injuries.long_comment: Stevens did not provide an updated timetable for Porzingis, but he said he's been surprised with how quick he's improving. The Celtics originally gave Porzingis a 5-to-6 month timetable, and the center told ESPN's Ramona Shelburne that he's expecting to return in December. With Porzingis trending in the right direction, he'll offer plenty of appeal as a stash pick in fantasy drafts.
injuries.short_comment: Brad Stevens said that Porzingis (foot) is making good progress since his foot surgery back in June, Jared Weiss of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Turner will sit for the club's preseason matchup, though he is expected to be back in full by Opening Night. The big man's absence will allow the Pacers an extended look at Jarace Walker and James Wiseman with Isaiah Jackson (hamstring) out.
injuries.short_comment: Turner (knee) has been ruled out for Tuesday's preseason opener versus the Hawks.

injuries.long_comment: Quickley will miss his second straight preseason contest while dealing with a left thumb sprain. His next chance to suit up is Sunday's preseason matchup with Boston.
injuries.short_comment: Quickley (thumb) won't play in Friday's preseason game versus the Wizards, Josh Lewenberg of TSN.ca reports.

injuries.long_comment: Harris will miss a second straight exhibition due to an illness. His next chance to make his Pistons debut will come Friday in Phoenix.
injuries.short_comment: Harris (illness) won't play in Tuesday's preseason game against the Suns, Omari Sankofa II of the Detroit Free Press reports.

injuries.long_comment: Claxton will sit for the preseason opener and could be a limited participant throughout the preseason. The 25-year-old will likely be good to go for the regular season, but the Nets will see what they have for depth at the five with Day'Ron Sharpe and Noah Clowney before the start of the year.
injuries.short_comment: Coach Jordi Fernandez said Friday that Claxton will miss Tuesday's preseason opener against the Clippers due to hamstring soreness, C.J. Holmes of the New York Daily News reports.

injuries.long_comment: Herro is coming off an injury-plagued 2023-24 campaign, during which he made a career-low 42 regular-season appearances. The hope is that it's a minor injury and Herro will be back on the court soon. However, Herro has never played in more than 67 regular-season games in a season, so this is still a concerning update. The Heat have five preseason games before starting the regular season against the Magic on Oct. 23.
injuries.short_comment: Herro won't play in Tuesday's preseason game against the  Hornets due to a right groin strain.

injuries.long_comment: Vassell needed a second surgery on his right foot in late June and will be cautious during rehab this time. "It just didn't heal how it was supposed to heal," Vassell said about his foot following his first surgery, which ended his 2023-24 campaign. "I don't want to rush back into it and have another setback," Vassell concluded. The young star will miss the start of the 2024-25 campaign, opening up more minutes for rookie Stephon Castle, but once he's fully healthy, Vassell should be a go-to player alongside Victor Wembanyama. Across 68 regular-season appearances last season, Vassell averaged 19.5 points, 4.1 assists, 3.8 rebounds and 1.1 steals in 33.1 minutes.
injuries.short_comment: Vassell (foot) will be re-evaluated Nov. 1, Tom Orsborn of the San Antonio Express-News reports.

injuries.long_comment: Ingram practiced Wednesday and "is fine" in the words of coach Willie Green. His exclusion from the majority of preseason contests appears to merely be veteran treatment for the 27-year-old.
injuries.short_comment: Ingram (undisclosed) will not play until New Orleans' preseason finale Tuesday versus Houston, Christian Clark of The New Orleans Times-Picayune reports.

injuries.long_comment: Williams played just 19 games in the 2022-2023 season due to a back injury. He was seemingly on track for a healthy training camp prior to this new injury. The big man projects to start at center for Charlotte when healthy, but it now looks like he will miss most of training camp. Look for the Hornets to err on the side of caution with the big man in order to avoid another season of a lingering injury.
injuries.short_comment: Williams (back) has suffered a tendon strain in his left foot and will be re-evaluated in two weeks, Tim Bontemps of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Bogdanovic will get an extra day of rest Tuesday, with Dyson Daniels getting the start at shooting guard. Bogdanovic is returning from a busy offseason, during which he helped Serbia win a bronze medal in the Olympic Games. The 32-year-old's absence will allow the Hawks to take an extended look at Daniels in the starting lineup, as well as Vit Krejci and Garrison Matthews off the bench.
injuries.short_comment: Bogdanovic (rest) has been ruled out of Tuesday's preseason opener against the Pacers, Brad Rowland of the Locked On Podcast Network reports.

injuries.long_comment: Okongwu still appears to be recovering from a non-surgical procedure he underwent in April to deal with inflammation in his left big toe. While Okongwu hasn't been ruled out for the preseason, his status is worth monitoring ahead of Atlanta's regular-season campaign, which begins Oct. 23 against Brooklyn.
injuries.short_comment: Okongwu (toe) is out for Tuesday's preseason opener against the Pacers, Brad Rowland of the Locked On Podcast Network reports.

injuries.long_comment: Porter will join Aaron Gordon (undisclosed), Russell Westbrook (rest) and DeAndre Jordan (rest) on the sidelines Sunday -- none of whom are expected to miss any time to begin the regular season. Porter started in Friday's 107-103 loss to the Celtics, during which he saw 15 minutes of action while scoring 12 points and shooting 5-for-8 from the field. The 26-year-old's next chance to suit up will come Sunday against the Suns.
injuries.short_comment: Porter (rest) will not play in Sunday's preseason game against the Celtics in Abu Dhabi, Harrison Wind of TheDNVR.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Middleton will be sidelined as he continues to nurse ankle injuries. Middleton has been trending in the right direction, but has not returned to practice in full, so it is unlikely he suits up in the near future.
injuries.short_comment: Middleton (ankle) will not play in Sunday's preseason game against the Pistons, Eric Nehm of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Murphy strained his right hamstring during Wednesday's training camp practice. The 24-year-old forward's status for the beginning of the regular season is now in question. Murphy is expected to compete with Herbert Jones for backup forward minutes when healthy.
injuries.short_comment: The Pelicans announced Thursday that Murphy has been diagnosed with a right hamstring strain and will be re-examined in approximately three weeks.

injuries.long_comment: Powell started in each of the Clippers' first two preseason contests but could be forced to sit out Friday. If Powell is unable to suit up against Portland, Kris Dunn, Amir Coffey and Nicolas Batum are candidates to enter the starting lineup.
injuries.short_comment: Powell's status for Friday's preseason game versus the Trail Blazers is uncertain due to an undisclosed reason, Law Murray of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: One week to the night of being dealt from New York to Minnesota, Randle is not ready to make his debut against the team that drafted him. This is unsurprising, as the big man was expected to be limited during the preseason as he recovers from a shoulder injury. When healthy, he is expected to start alongside Rudy Gobert in the frontcourt. In his absence Friday, Naz Reid is the likely candidate to start.
injuries.short_comment: Randle (shoulder) will be held out of Friday's preseason opener versus the Lakers, Dave McMenamin of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Nurkic's finger injury will keep him out of Phoenix's preseason opener. However, there is no indication that the 30-year-old big man will be forced to miss any regular-season action.
injuries.short_comment: The Suns announced Saturday that Nurkic won't play in Sunday's preseason opener against the Lakers due to a left middle finger and will be re-evaluated in one week, Kellan Olson of ArizonaSports.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Allen's absence is not expected to affect his availability for Opening Night, and with the 28-year-old out the Suns will likely get an extended look at Damion Lee, Boo Buie and Collin Gillespie. Allen's next opportunity to suit up will come at home Friday against the Pistons.
injuries.short_comment: Allen (personal) has been ruled out for Tuesday's preseason matchup against the Pistons, Kellan Olson of ArizonaSports.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Barrett sustained a sprain to his right acromioclavicular joint during the second quarter of Sunday's preseason over the Wizards. It's unclear if Barrett will be available for Opening Night against the Cavaliers on Oct. 23, but there should be at least some optimism given the injury is to his right, non-shooting shoulder. Regardless, fantasy managers should monitor Barrett's situation closely ahead of drafts and may have to drop him down a couple of ranks if he's going to miss regular-season action.
injuries.short_comment: Barrett (shoulder) will miss the remainder of the preseason, Brett Siegel of ClutchPoints.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Presumably, the Mavericks are just being cautious with four starters getting the night off. Washington should be considered questionable for Thursday's preseason game against Utah. In 29 regular-season games for Dallas in 2023-24, Washington averaged 11.7 points, 6.2 rebounds, 1.5 assists, 1.2 steals and 0.9 blocks.
injuries.short_comment: Washington will not play in Monday's preseason game against Memphis due to left hip tightness.

injuries.long_comment: Thomson continues to recover from treatment for a blood clot and has been limited in training camp. While Thompson's next chance to suit up is Friday's preseason rematch with Phoenix, he will need to be medically cleared before taking the floor.
injuries.short_comment: Thompson (illness) has yet to be cleared by the NBA and won't play in Tuesday's preseason contest against the Suns, Omari Sankofa II of the Detroit Free Press reports.

injuries.long_comment: Carter's next opportunity to suit up for preseason action comes Oct. 18 versus Philadelphia, as Friday's game against New Orleans has been canceled due to inclement weather in the area. Orlando will likely exercise an abundance of precaution with the 25-year-old ramping up in advance of the regular season.
injuries.short_comment: Carter (ankle) is out for Wednesday's preseason game versus San Antonio.

injuries.long_comment: Brown will be re-evaluated in three weeks, meaning he is more than likely to be held out of the team's preseason opener against the Wizards on Oct. 6. The 28-year-old said that the lingering knee issue affected his play starting in December of last season, during which he averaged 10.8 points, 4.2 rebounds and 2.9 assists across 27.9 minutes in 67 appearances (44 starts). If Brown misses additional time, Gradey Dick (ankle) will likely pick up extra minutes and could secure the starting job.
injuries.short_comment: The Raptors announced Brown underwent arthroscopic surgery on his right knee, and he will be re-evaluated in three weeks, Ryan Wolstat of the Toronto Sun reports.

injuries.long_comment: Robinson is coming off two procedures on his left ankle, with the most recent surgery taking place on May 14. According to Begley, a return in December or January could be on the table depending on how the rehab process goes, as neither Robinson or the Knicks want to rush the process to make sure that the center is at full strength before getting clearance. With Robinson sidelined to begin the season, Julius Randle could spend a lot of time at center in smaller lineups, while Precious Achiuwa and Jericho Sims will have a lot more opportunity to earn meaningful minutes.
injuries.short_comment: Robinson (ankle) will not be ready for the beginning of the NBA season, Ian Begley of SportsNet New York reports.

injuries.long_comment: Gordon is dealing with a minor injury, though it is likely nothing that will prevent him from seeing the floor during the preseason. The 29-year-old is expected to play limited minutes when he comes back so the team can further evaluate its second unit, but this will likely not be the case to begin the regular season. Gordon's next opportunity to suit up during the preseason will come Sunday against the Suns.
injuries.short_comment: Gordon is dealing with a minor, undisclosed injury and will not suit up for Sunday's preseason game against the Celtics, Bennett Durando of The Denver Post reports.

injuries.long_comment: Jones' next opportunity for preseason reps comes Saturday versus Utah. Stephon Castle, Malachi Flynn and Blake Wesley represent depth options with extra opportunities to prove themselves Wednesday.
injuries.short_comment: Jones (rest) will not play Wednesday versus Orlando, Tom Orsborn of the San Antonio Express-News reports.

injuries.long_comment: Brogdon suffered the injury during Saturday's practice, but now there's a bit more clarity. While a timetable hasn't been officially announced, previous reports suggested he will miss at least a month of action. In his absence, guys like Bilal Coulibaly, Corey Kispert and Carlton Carrington could see more opportunity in the backcourt.
injuries.short_comment: Brogdon underwent surgery Tuesday to repair a torn ligament in his right thumb, Josh Robbins of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Strus is dealing with a right hip contusion suffered in Tuesday's preseason match against Chicago. The 28-year-old's status will need to be monitored.
injuries.short_comment: Strus (hip) did not practice Wednesday in advance of Thursday's preseason contest against Indiana, Chris Fedor of The Cleveland Plain Dealer reports.

injuries.long_comment: Avdija is missing Friday's contest in Los Angeles, the first of three preseason opportunities before the Blazers tip off the regular season at home vs. Golden State. His next chance to play would be Sunday evening against the Kings.
injuries.short_comment: Avdija (personal) will not play in Friday's preseason game against the Clippers.

injuries.long_comment: Sharpe will miss the beginning of the regular season due to his left shoulder injury. Deni Avdija, Toumani Camara, Kris Murray and Dalano Banton are candidates to receive increased playing time in his absence. Sharpe will likely be one of Portland's primary bench options when available.
injuries.short_comment: The Trail Blazers announced Saturday that Sharpe has suffered a small posterior labral tear in his left shoulder and is expected to miss 4-6 weeks.

injuries.long_comment: Per Anthony Chiang of the Miami Herald, the hope is that Jaquez's injury is minor and he'll be back on the court soon. Following Tuesday's game, the Heat return home to face the Hawks. Miami has five preseason games before opening the regular season against the Magic on Oct. 23.
injuries.short_comment: Jaquez won't play in Tuesday's preseason game against the Hornets due to a left groin strain.

injuries.long_comment: Huerter has been increasingly more involved at practice, but he's yet to be cleared for 5-on-5 activities and will be unavailable for the Kings' preseason opener. Huerter is recovering from a procedure in April that repaired his torn left labrum.  While the 26-year-old seems close to gaining 5-on-5 clearance, it's unknown when he'll be ready to play in games. Sacramento's next exhibition comes Friday at Golden State.
injuries.short_comment: Huerter (shoulder) has been ruled out for Wednesday's preseason game against the Warriors.

injuries.long_comment: Trent hyperextended his left elbow during Sunday's preseason opener against the Pistons but may not miss any time. Trent didn't need an MRI, and Rivers suspects the shooting guard will be back in action Thursday against the Lakers, but the coach wouldn't guarantee it.
injuries.short_comment: Coach Doc Rivers said Trent (elbow) didn't practice Tuesday but is expected to be fine, Eric Nehm of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Johnson is joined by Tre Jones as healthy scratches Wednesday. Johnson's next opportunity for preseason action comes Saturday versus Utah.
injuries.short_comment: Johnson (rest) will not play Wednesday versus Orlando, Tom Orsborn of the San Antonio Express-News reports.

injuries.long_comment: Despite fully returning to practice, Wiggins will likely miss Golden State's first four preseason outings while recovering from an illness. However, there is no indication that Wiggins will be unavailable once the regular season rolls around.
injuries.short_comment: Coach Steve Kerr said Thursday that Wiggins (illness) won't play in Friday's preseason game versus the Kings and is unlikely to suit up for Sunday's preseason matchup with Detroit, Dalton Johnson of NBC Sports Bay Area reports.

injuries.long_comment: Vanderbilt had procedures on both feet during the offseason, and there's been some optimism that he could be ready to face Minnesota on Oct. 22 to open the season. Vanderbilt said his rehab process has been going great, and it will be interesting to see how he progresses throughout the preseason.
injuries.short_comment: Vanderbilt (foot) said Monday that he's not sure if he'll be ready for Opening Night, Jovan Buha of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: After a solid all-around preseason debut with the Nuggets, Westbrook will take Sunday off. The All-Star's absence will likely allow coach Mike Malone to get a better look at Trey Alexander and Jalen Pickett. However, when the regular season begins Westbrook is expected to be the second man up behind Jamal Murray at point guard.
injuries.short_comment: Westbrook (rest) will not play in Sunday's preseason game against the Celtics, Bennett Durando of The Denver Post reports.

injuries.long_comment: McBride's absence will give way to Cameron Payne and rookie Tyler Kolek as primary ballhandlers, while Landry Shamet could see more action as well. McBride's next opportunity for preseason action comes Sunday versus Minnesota.
injuries.short_comment: McBride will miss New York's preseason game Wednesday versus Washington due to an illness, James L. Edwards III of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Richardson is in the final stages of his recovery from a right shoulder injury he suffered back in February, which he underwent surgery for in early March. The Heat are taking the cautious approach, and Richardson may not see the floor until the regular-season opener against the Magic on Oct. 23. Across 43 games (six starts) in the 2023-24 regular season, he averaged 9.9 points, 2.8 rebounds and 2.4 assists across 25.7 minutes per game.
injuries.short_comment: Richardson (shoulder) will not play in Tuesday's preseason game against the Hornets.

injuries.long_comment: Watson averaged 6.7 points, 3.2 rebounds, 1.1 assists and 1.1 blocks in 18.6 minutes across 80 regular-season appearances in 2023-24. Now, the third-year forward is set to take on an even bigger role and stay in Denver for at least two more years.
injuries.short_comment: The Nuggets picked up Watson's (hamstring) team option for 2025-26 on Thursday, Keith Smith of Spotrac.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Jackson has been limited in practice since Oct. 4, but the Pacers have yet to clarify what injury he's dealing with. Jackson's next chance to play is Thursday against the Cavaliers.
injuries.short_comment: During an appearance on The Wake Up Call, Pacers coach Rick Carlisle said Jackson (undisclosed) will not play in Tuesday's preseason game against the Hawks.

injuries.long_comment: Thybulle appears to have fully recovered from the ankle impingement that caused him to miss the end of the 2023-24 campaign but is now dealing with a knee issue. His status for Friday's preseason opener against the Clippers is uncertain.
injuries.short_comment: Thybulle won't participate in Saturday's Fan Fest due to right knee soreness and will undergo further evaluation, Aaron J. Fentress of The Oregonian reports.

injuries.long_comment: After an injury-plagued 2023-24 campaign that saw Williams make just six appearances, he is already off to a rough start in 204-25. While Williams could return in time for Portland's regular-season opener against Golden State on Oct. 23, hamstring injuries can often linger.
injuries.short_comment: The Trail Blazers announced Friday that Williams experienced a grade 1 left hamstring strain during training camp and he is expected to miss two weeks.

injuries.long_comment: While Williams is expected to make a full recovery, he will almost certainly miss all of training camp and the preseason. The 24-year-old forward could remain sidelined for Memphis' regular-season opener on Oct. 23 against Utah. Williams is slated to be one of the Grizzlies' top forward options off the bench when healthy this season.
injuries.short_comment: The Grizzlies announced Thursday that imaging has revealed a stress reaction in the upper portion of Williams' tibia and he will be re-evaluated in approximately four weeks.

injuries.long_comment: Bogdanovic said his wrist isn't really an issue anymore, but his surgically-repaired foot is still on the mend. He'll be able to do some on-court stuff during training camp, but he hasn't been cleared for 5-on-5 yet and it sounds like the Nets are prepared to take a cautious approach with the veteran to open the season.
injuries.short_comment: Bogdanovic (foot) said Monday that he remains without a timetable for a return, C.J. Holmes of the New York Daily News reports.

injuries.long_comment: This is a brutal blow for the Nets, as Sharpe is one of the most reliable backup centers in the NBA. Trendon Watford is also battling a hamstring strain and is expected to miss a couple weeks. Based on Sharpe's timetable, the earliest he could return is Nov. 19 against the Hornets. Noah Clowney could see increased run to open the season as a result, while Nic Claxton could have a higher floor in fantasy basketball.
injuries.short_comment: Sharpe will miss at least six weeks with a left hamstring strain, Brett Siegel of ClutchPoints.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: While Ball will not make his long awaited return Saturday, head coach Billy Donovan said that Ball is still working on a slow build up into game readiness, meaning he may come back soon. If held out, his next chance to suit up will be Monday against Milwaukee.
injuries.short_comment: Ball (knee) is not likely to play in Saturday's preseason game against the Grizzlies, Julia Poe of the Chicago Tribune reports.

injuries.long_comment: Collins is still working his way back from shoulder surgery in April. He was able to participate in 5-on-5 drills during training camp, so Collins may return to game action before the preseason ends. His next chance to do so will come Saturday versus Utah.
injuries.short_comment: Collins (rest/shoulder) won't play in Wednesday's preseason game against the Magic, Michael C. Wright of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Williams will miss his second consecutive preseason game due to a minor right hamstring injury, though he is expected to return in full for Opening Night. The 25-year-old's absence will likely allow the Hornets to take an extended look at Harry Giles and Moussa Diabate behind Miles Bridges and Nick Richards.
injuries.short_comment: Williams (hamstring) has been ruled out of Tuesday's preseason matchup against the Heat.

injuries.long_comment: The forward will be re-evaluated in eight weeks, meaning he will miss the start of the 2024-25 season. This is a tough blow for Wood, as it will set him back with his offseason training. Wood exercised his $3.04 million player option back in May and was already facing an uphill battle for playing time, and this certainly won't help.
injuries.short_comment: Wood underwent a successful arthroscopic surgical procedure on his left knee Monday, Mike Trudell of Spectrum SportsNet reports.

injuries.long_comment: Bamba appears unlikely to suit up this preseason while dealing with a knee injury. While Bamba is hoping to be available once the regular season rolls around, Kai Jones will serve as the team's backup center in his absence.
injuries.short_comment: Coach Tyronn Lue said Thursday that Bamba (knee) is hopeful to be ready for the Clippers' regular-season opener against Phoenix on Oct. 23, Law Murray of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Hyland will sit Tuesday, though it is just expected to be a precautionary move by the club ahead of Opening Night. The 24-year-old's next chance to suit up during the preseason will come Friday versus the Trail Blazers.
injuries.short_comment: Hyland will be held out of Tuesday's preseason matchup versus the Nets due to left hip soreness, Law Murray of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Jackson will miss at least the first month of the season while rehabbing from the procedure but is expected to make a full recovery. However, when healthy, his role remains unclear. As a rookie, the second-round pick carved out a substantial role for the injury-riddled Grizzlies. Over his final 18 regular-season appearances, Jackson averaged 20.4 points, 5.0 rebounds and 2.1 assists in 34.1 minutes per game. With Ja Morant (shoulder), Marcus Smart (finger) and Desmond Bane (back) returning to full strength this offseason, Jackson will have a difficult time repeating those numbers in Year 2.
injuries.short_comment: Jackson underwent a successful procedure to repair a broken fifth metatarsal in his right foot Wednesday and will be evaluated in approximately three months.

injuries.long_comment: Exum suffered this injury during training camp, and while a timetable has yet to be announced, he's likely going to miss significant time. This is a tough blow for Dallas, as Exum was solid last season with averages of 7.8 points, 2.9 assists and 2.7 rebounds in 55 regular-season appearances. Guys like Jaden Hardy, Naji Marshall and Quentin Grimes could see a bump in minutes with this news.
injuries.short_comment: Exum underwent surgery on his right wrist Tuesday, Grant Afseth of EssentiallySports.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Lyles is battling through a groin injury he suffered during offseason workouts, which has kept him out of training camp. The hope for Lyles is he will be available for the start of the 2024-25 regular season, though his minutes could be restricted as he catches up on his conditioning. He's slated to provide frontcourt depth behind Domantas Sabonis, Keegan Murray and Alex Len.
injuries.short_comment: Lyles (groin) walked through the offense with coaches following Wednesday's practice session, Matt George of ABC 10 Sacramento reports.

injuries.long_comment: Bey is coming off a down year in which he converted a career-low  31.6 percent of his three-point attempts across 63 games with the Hawks, but maybe a change of scenery will help him rediscover his sharpshooting ways. Unfortunately, he's still rehabbing from an ACL tear that he suffered in March, so it's unlikely he'll be ready for the start of the 2024-25 season.
injuries.short_comment: Bey has agreed to a three-year, $20 million contract with the Wizards, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.

injuries.long_comment: Hayes was a late addition to the injury report, and the severity of his hip injury is unknown. The 23-year-old's next opportunity to feature will come Monday versus the Wizards.
injuries.short_comment: Hayes (hip) has been ruled out of Tuesday's preseason opener against the Clippers, C.J. Holmes of the New York Daily News reports.

injuries.long_comment: Martin continues to deal with a wrist sprain that will keep him out for Charlotte's first two preseason contests. His next chance to suit up is Thursday's preseason matchup with Memphis.
injuries.short_comment: Martin (wrist) won't play in Tuesday's preseason game against the Heat.

injuries.long_comment: Sims' night was over right after it started, suffering the injury in his second minute of play. The center didn't record any counting stats. The severity of the sprain is unclear, but his next chance to play will come Sunday against the Timberwolves.
injuries.short_comment: Sims exited Wednesday's 117-94 preseason win over the Wizards after sustaining a sprained ankle, Kristian Winfield of the New York Daily News reports.

injuries.long_comment: With Tuesday's contest almost over, it seems unlikely Lee will check back in. As things stand, he is set to finish with one rebound and one steal in five minutes of action. Lee's next chance to suit up is Friday's preseason rematch with Detroit.
injuries.short_comment: Lee went to the locker room with 8:49 remaining in the fourth quarter of Tuesday's preseason game against the Pistons after taking a hit to the groin/leg area, Gerald Bourguet of GoPHNX.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Adams is joined by fellow veteran Fred VanVleet as healthy scratches Wednesday. His next opportunity for preseason action comes Tuesday versus New Orleans.
injuries.short_comment: Adams (rest) will not play in Wednesday's preseason game versus Oklahoma City, Jonathan Feigen of the Houston Chronicle reports.

injuries.long_comment: It's unclear if Williams will miss any regular-season action, but hamstring injuries can often linger. With Kenrich Williams (knee) also out, Ousmane Dieng could receive increased playing time early on off the bench in Oklahoma City's frontcourt.
injuries.short_comment: The Thunder announced Thursday that Williams is out with a right hamstring strain and will be re-evaluated after the preseason, Brandon Rahbar of DailyThunder.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Carter sustained his left shoulder injury during a pre-draft workout, and the Kings were aware of the issue when selecting him with the 13th overall pick in the 2024 NBA Draft. The Kings announced Thursday that they'll update his status in approximately six months, so the 22-year-old will presumably miss at least the first few months of the 2024-25 season. However, Carter is expected to make a full recovery with no long-term concerns.
injuries.short_comment: The Kings announced Thursday that Carter underwent successful surgery to repair a torn labrum in his left shoulder, Jason Anderson of The Sacramento Bee reports.

injuries.long_comment: Bassey is working his way back from a torn ACL in his left knee that he sustained last December. Coach Greg Popovich said Monday that Bassey returned to 5-on-5 drills during training camp, so he may return to game action before the preseason ends.
injuries.short_comment: Bassey (knee) won't play in Wednesday's preseason game against the Magic, Michael C. Wright of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Kleber has yet to return to practice after tweaking his ankle early on in training camp. With so much competition in the frontcourt, Kleber is looking at a minimal role at best this season.
injuries.short_comment: Kleber (ankle) will not play in Monday's preseason game against Memphis.

injuries.long_comment: Williams underwent right knee surgery in September, so it does not come as a surprise that he won't suit up Monday. The 29-year-old likely won't appear in the preseason, though he has returned to practice in a limited fashion which bodes well for his chance to return to game action soon.
injuries.short_comment: Williams (knee) has been ruled out for Monday's preseason opener against the Spurs, Nick Gallo of the Thunder's official site reports.

injuries.long_comment: Fresh off inking a one-year deal over the summer, McLaughlin's start to the season will not be what he had in mind. When healthy, he is expected to compete with Keon Ellis for the backup point guard role behind De'Aaron Fox. The 28-year-old shot a career-best 47.2 percent from three-point range across 56 games in Minnesota last season to go along with 3.5 points and 1.3 rebounds across 11.2 minutes.
injuries.short_comment: McLaughlin sustained a grade 2 right ankle sprain during off-season workouts and will be re-evaluated in two weeks, James Ham of ESPN 1320 Sacramento reports.

injuries.long_comment: The No. 35 pick in the 2024 NBA Draft, Furphy tweaked his ankle last week and has been limited in practice since. He's considered day-to-day, however, so it's possible he debuts Thursday against the Cavaliers.
injuries.short_comment: During an appearance on The Wake Up Call, Pacers coach Rick Carlisle said Furphy (ankle) won't play in Tuesday's preseason game against the Hawks.

injuries.long_comment: Klintman has yet to play in a preseason game due to his calf injury. However, his next opportunity to play will be Friday in Phoenix.
injuries.short_comment: Klintman (calf) will stay sidelined from preseason action Tuesday night against the Suns.

injuries.long_comment: The Nets also announced that Day'Ron Sharpe (hamstring) will miss at least six weeks. With both these players sidelined, Noah Clowney could see increased reps as the backup center if he has a strong showing in the preseason.
injuries.short_comment: Watford will miss at least two weeks with a left hamstring strain, Brett Siegel of ClutchPoints.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Robinson is dealing with a left knee injury, but a formal diagnosis has yet to be revealed. His next opportunity for preseason action comes Friday in a rematch against Golden State.
injuries.short_comment: Robinson (knee) will not play in Wednesday's preseason game versus Golden State.

injuries.long_comment: Jordan played limited run in Denver's preseason opener, and he will take Sunday off. This will allow coach Mike Malone to get a better look at Zeke Nnaji and Dario Saric behind Nikola Jokic. Jordan's next opportunity to play will come Sunday versus the Suns.
injuries.short_comment: Jordan (rest) won't play in Sunday's preseason game against the Celtics, Bennett Durando of The Denver Post reports.

injuries.long_comment: Smith sustained the injury near the end of training camp, and it is unclear whether he will be back for Opening Night of the regular season. The 20-year-old is coming off a decent, but somewhat inconsistent rookie season, during which he averaged 5.9 points, 1.4 rebounds and 1.2 assists across 14.3 minutes per game in 51 regular-season outings. If Smith is out for an extended period of time, KJ Simpson and Vasilije Micic are both candidates to pick up minutes.
injuries.short_comment: Smith sustained a left groin injury during training camp and will miss Sunday's preseason opener against the Knicks -- he will be reevaluated in one week.

injuries.long_comment: The first-round pick of the 2024 Draft will not be permitted to participate in on-court activities for at least a week of training camp due to the shoulder injury. However, Walter is not likely to miss any time in the regular-season, and the Raptors are expected to give an update on his status after one week. The 20-year-old played for Baylor in 2023-24, during which he averaged 14.5 points, 4.5 rebounds, 1.4 assists and 1.1 steals across 32.2 minutes per game in 35 regular-season appearances.
injuries.short_comment: Walter sprained his acromioclavicular joint (shoulder) during informal workouts and will not participate in on-court activities to start training camp, Tim Bontemps of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: It's unclear exactly when Dadiet picked up the injury, but it prevented him from appearing in Wednesday's preseason opener. Despite being selected with the 25th overall pick in the 2024 NBA Draft, Dadiet isn't expected to be anything more than a fringe rotation piece this season. His next chance to play will come Sunday against the Timberwolves.
injuries.short_comment: Dadiet didn't play in Wednesday's 117-94 preseason win over the Wizards due to a  sprained finger, Kristian Winfield of the New York Daily News reports

injuries.long_comment: Bates will be re-evaluated in approximately one month, by which point a timeline for his return to basketball activities should be more clear. The 2023 second-round pick spent most of his rookie season with the G League Cleveland Charge, and across 18 games he averaged 19.8 points, 5.9 rebounds and 2.0 assists across 34.6 minutes per game. He did appear in 15 games for the Cavaliers during the 2023-24 regular season and averaged 2.7 points across 8.9 minutes per game.
injuries.short_comment: Bates underwent surgery Wednesday to repair a torn meniscus in his right knee, Spencer Davies of SI.com reports.
